This paper is about a ranking model that uses reinforcement learning to incorporate mutual interactions among documents. The main application of this model is in information retrieval, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Markov Decision Process and NDCG, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as document similarity, which is a topic in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses datasets and experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed model, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
